[normal]My clients have instructed me to write further to you on the subject of your report and the impression it gives that their activities have somehow threatened the ability of democratic government on Sark to operate fairly and robustly.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]They
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]say that this is very far from the truth and have asked me to send to you the attached diagram which they believe summarises the true state of affairs on Sark.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] The reference to SEM at the side of the graph is "Sark Estate Management".
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] This is the organisation which runs Barclay affairs on Sark.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]You will see that my clients maintain that political power on Sark is in fact held by the unelected 
[normal]Seigneur
[normal], the unelected Seneschal and the Chairman of the General Purposes Committee, Charles Maitland, himself not directly elected by the people of Sark to that position.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] My clients point out that they have no influence or control over any of these office holders.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] They further point out that they regard themselves as having no representation in Chief Pleas itself.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] There 
[normal]is no constituency system and 
[normal]Brecqhou
[normal] has no separate representation.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] Indeed they
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]see themselves as having no political power in Sark at all and therefore find it extremely surprising that it should be suggested that they threaten democracy on that Island.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]My clients believe that the true history of Sark politics and what passes for democracy over the last few years has been the domination of Sark by a clique which has the 
[normal]Seigneur
[normal] and the Seneschal at its centre.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] The reforms which took place in Sark have affected matters hardly at all.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] Indeed the 
[normal]Seigneur
[normal] continues to sit on a dais in Chief Pleas with his appointee for life, the Seneschal, at his side, controlling and conducting the business of Chief Pleas.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]By way of illustration only I outline the nature of the Seneschal's office:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]a)
[normal]              
[normal]it is unelected, whether directly or indirectly;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]b)
[normal]              
[normal]the holder is appointed by the unelected feudal overlord of Sark;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]c)
[normal]              
[normal]no retirement age is specified;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]d)
[normal]              
[normal]the holder cannot be removed from office by Chief Pleas, only by the (again unelected) Lieutenant-Governor and then only "for good cause";
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]e)
[normal]              
[normal]the holder has considerable powers over Chief Pleas, as evidenced by the Reform Law and the Rules of Procedure.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] The Seneschal
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]draws up the Agenda and controls the order of business, which can have a significant effect on how business is in fact disposed of.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He controls the debate, the order of speakers, the length of debate, when a vote is taken and
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]whether a named vote is allowed.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He has a considerable discretion as to the application of the rules and whether there are
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]in fact any rules for any given issue;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]f)
[normal]              
[normal]the Seneschal operates in a parliament with
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]no organised political parties,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]and no ministerial system; there is no true Chief Minister or opposition leader, all 
[normal]Conseillers
[normal] are, in effect, at the Seneschal's beck and call, there is a sense in which he is the true Chief Minister as well as being
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Speaker;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]g)
[normal]              
[normal]he controls the calling of meetings, indeed his consent is required in some circumstances
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]to call a meeting (for example when 
[normal]Conseillers
[normal] request that an
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]extraordinary
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]meeting take place);
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]h)
[normal]              
[normal]he is the returning officer for elections;
[normal]i
[normal])
[normal]              
[normal]he is the principal judge in both criminal and civil matters; he decides both issues of fact and law sitting alone and without any legal qualification;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]j)
[normal]              
[normal]he is one of the three
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]trustees of Sark's publicly owned assets,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the other two being more junior officers of Chief Pleas;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]k)
[normal]              
[normal]the present incumbent has a personal manner which is
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]powerful and domineering.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As a matter of law
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the Seneschal
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]has no vote and is supposed to have no voice, but in practice he frequently speaks beyond the limits of his role of President and is politically active outside of Chief Pleas as evidenced
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]by the memorandum he submitted to your Committee and comments he has made in the past, particularly after the December 2008 elections.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] His personal opposition to my clients is well known; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]l)
[normal]              
[normal]the Seneschal is, in many respects, the central focus of Sark politics.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He works closely with the 
[normal]Seigneur
[normal] and the Committee Presidents.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He works closely with the Guernsey authorities.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] All legislation passes through his hands.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He reports to the Guernsey authorities after each Chief Pleas meeting; 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In summary,
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]the Seneschal is the 
[normal]Seigneur's
[normal] appointee and man.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He controls Sark politics, Sark's justice system, Sark's electoral system, Sark's 
[normal]conveyancing
[normal] system, Sark's liquor licensing system and is the dominant trustee of the publicly owned assets.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] He is unelected by the people and unaccountable to them whilst having strongly held and very publicly known political views opposing
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]my clients.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Notwithstanding the 
[normal]unappealed
[normal] judgment of the English Court of Appeal from as long ago as 2
[normal]nd
[normal] December 2008 that the Seneschal's role breaches Article 6 of the European Convention on Human Rights, Sark has still failed to introduce legislation (even in draft) to reform his office and separate his judicial and legislative roles.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] Indeed when the issue was considered by Chief Pleas on 14
[normal]th
[normal] April the matter was placed at item 20 of a 31 item agenda, by the Seneschal.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] This is another powerful indicator of the Sark's establishment's disregard for true
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]democracy and an indication of where the real problem lies.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal] As noted before, without the consistent pressure brought to bear by my clients, there would be no democracy on Sark, not even the seriously flawed version that exists today.
[normal]&#xa0;
